---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="The editorial stance behind AI Adoption Blueprint: practical, skeptical, production-focused guidance for serious AI adoption."
>
  <section class="shell section">
    <div class="prose">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Practical guidance for the work after the demo.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        AI Adoption Blueprint is for architects, CTOs, product leaders, and
        adoption teams trying to turn AI experiments into durable operating
        capability.
      </p>
      <h2>What this is</h2>
      <p>
        This site focuses on workflow design, data access, permissions,
        evaluation, observability, security, governance, and ROI. The goal is to
        help serious builders make better adoption decisions.
      </p>
      <h2>What this is not</h2>
      <p>
        This is not an AI news site, prompt library, or hype channel. Models and
        tools matter, but production AI usually fails or succeeds because of the
        system around the model.
      </p>
      <h2>Editorial stance</h2>
      <p>
        The voice here is direct, candid, and humble. Strong claims should be
        grounded in evidence, experience, or a clearly labeled opinion. Useful
        pages should leave the reader with a checklist, decision rule, workflow
        map, or architecture pattern they can apply.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

